&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIALTY DOCTOR IN OPHTHALMOLOGY FIXED TERM &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working hours: 10 Programmed Activities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity within our busy ophthalmic department with a comprehensive range of sub specialties, covering both 6 and 12 month contracts. You will be a key member of an enthusiastic team of medical staff providing a quality service to a busy department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be full time appointments (10 PAs) and the job plans are designed to undertake a range of clinics appropriate to experience and interest. There are also opportunities for surgery (theatre session and Intravitreal injection sessions) and laser depending upon skills and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will join a team of 8 consultants, 1 Associate Specialist, 2 SAS doctors, 1 trust grade and 3 SpRs, supported by a team of Orthoptists and Optometrists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our large Ophthalmology department is situated in the Westminster Eye Unit and has access to an Ophthalmology ward area, main theatres and ophthalmology outpatient clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department has regular educational meetings and actively supports opportunities for personal development of appointed staff. Informal visits/discussions are encouraged and can be arranged by contacting Mr Kashif Ali’s secretary on 01244 362199.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr Kashif AliJob titleConsultant OphthalmologistEmail addresskashif.ali2@nhs.netTelephone number01244 362199Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
